==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scullion
<hw>Scul"lion</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>escouillon</ets> (Cot.)
a dishclout, apparently for <ets>escouvillon</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧couvillon</ets> a swab; cf. also OF. <ets>souillon</ets> a
servant employed for base offices. Cf. <er>Scovel</er>.]</ety> <def>A
servant who cleans pots and kettles, and does other menial services in
the kitchen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The meanest <qex>scullion</qex> that followed his camp.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scullionly</ent>⟦br⟧
